  "commentary": "With SPX at 7101.68 sitting just below the max negative gamma strike at 7115, dealers are likely covering short hedges and buying into this move, providing fuel for further upside momentum. The recent wall break event combined with 8.3% GEX increase suggests we've pushed through resistance, but the thick positive gamma wall at 7150 (+5965.2M) will create meaningful selling pressure as we approach that level. Watch for dealer selling to intensify between 7115-7150 as they hedge long gamma positions, with the ultimate magnet being the massive 7200 wall (+7535.0M) where selling pressure peaks.\n\nBottom line: expect a grind higher toward 7150 with increasing resistance.",
